dc_title_s: Map of the territory of the United States from the Mississippi to the Pacific Ocean; ordered by Jeff'n Davis, Secretary of War to accompany the reports of the explorations for a railroad route
dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Shows Indian tribal locations, military posts, and routes and dates of expeditions and surveys. Includes "Note" and "Authorities." Historic Maps copy 1 on 2 sheets designed to be joined together; uncolored. Historic Maps copy 2 dissected in 16 pieces, mounted on cloth.
dc_publisher_s: [Washington, D.C.] : Office of P.R.R. Surveys, War Dep., [1857]
